Cook pasta as directed on package, omitting salt. Meanwhile, heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add onions and garlic; cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp-tender. Add cream cheese product; cook and stir on medium heat 5 minutes or until melted. Whisk in broth and milk; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until slightly thickened. (Do not boil.) Drain pasta. Serve topped with sauce.